A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Human Relations – Discrimination in Housing – Income–Based Housing
3 Subsidies
4 FOR the purpose of providing that a certain landlord may not refuse to rent to a prospective
5 tenant who pays rent with the assistance of an income–based housing subsidy under
6 certain circumstances, subject to a certain exception; establishing that a violation of
7 this Act is a discriminatory housing practice and is subject to enforcement by the
8 Maryland Commission on Civil Rights; and generally relating to housing
9 discrimination.
